<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1269,2024]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1269,1294]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[305,414,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Holotype</typeStatus>
: 
<number box="[426,447,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="3.0">3</number>
. Length, 
<quantity box="[558,639,1269,1293]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[655,726,1269,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="28.[151,249,1902,1925]" captionTargetBox="[189,1388,184,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[189,1394,161,1885]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 3. Siobla species, dorsal view. a. S. reticulatia, holotype, Ƥ; b. S. reticulatia, non-type, 3; c. S. metallica, non-type, Ƥ; d. S. metallica, non-type, 3; e. S. obtusiscutellata sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ; f. S. bomeica sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ; g. S. obtusiscutellata sp. nov., paratype, 3; h. S. brevipilosa, sp. nov., holotype, 3; i. S. longipennis, sp. nov., holotype, Ƥ. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280108/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Figs 
<number box="[713,726,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
h, 
<number box="[757,773,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="6.0">6</number>
l). Body metallic blue, basal tergites and hind leg metallic purple; clypeus blackish brown; small lateral macula of 
<number box="[785,799,1308,1332]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tergite white. Tibiae, tarsi and anterior sides of femora of fore and middle legs and tibial spurs of each leg pale brown. Forewing infuscate hyaline, cell C dark brown, stigma and veins blackish brown, hind wing hyaline. Body hairs pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1269,2024]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Punctures on head dense (
<figureCitation box="[499,582,1416,1440]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="46.[151,249,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,220,1661]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[151,1436,193,1677]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 21. Siobla species, head (dorsal view), postocellar area and mesoscutellum (lateral view). a – c. S. brevipilosa, sp. nov., 3; d – f. S. sinica, sp. nov., Ƥ; g – i. S. sinica, sp. nov., 3; j – l. S. longipennis, sp. nov., Ƥ. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280125/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[553,582,1416,1440]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
a), punctures on clypeus small and sparse, interspaces shiny; punctures on temple shallow, distance between punctures about equal to diameter of punctures, interspaces shiny; postocellar area punctured with shiny interspaces; pronotum densely punctured; punctures on mesoscutum sparse, interspaces longer than diameter of punctures, punctures on anterior slope of mesoscutellum sparse, interspaces equal to diameter of punctures, posterior slope densely punctured; posttergite microsculptured; metascutellum punctured, interspaces microsculptured; upper half of mesepisternum coarsely and densely punctured, punctures on venter of mesepisternum small and sparse, interspaces microsculptured; recess of mesepimeron microsculptured, posterior margin of mesepimeron shiny and dorsum coarsely and densely punctured; dorsum of metepisternum densely punctured; middle and posterior of metepimeron shiny, dorsum densely punctured; 
<number box="[1128,1142,1707,1731]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
st abdominal tergite shiny except area near middle furrow with sparse and large punctures and lateral 
<number box="[1004,1014,1745,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1024,1040,1745,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="4.0">4</number>
of 
<number box="[1079,1093,1745,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
st tergite with dense punctures, other tergites microsculptured and shallowly punctured except 
<number box="[855,869,1784,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="8.0">8</number>
th tergite shiny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1269,2024]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,932]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Hairs on dorsum of head and thorax and mesoscutellum straight, as long as transverse diameter of median ocellus; hairs on other parts of thorax shorter than transverse diameter of median ocellus; hairs on mesepisternum straight, slightly longer than transverse diameter of median ocellus. Anterior margin of clypeus truncate; malar space linear; head in front view with eyes converging below, lower interocular distance 
<number box="[1149,1184,1928,1952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="0.8">0.8</number>
× eye height; anterior margin of supraantennal tubercle elevated; middle fovea deep and broad, smaller than frons; frontal ridge narrow and obtuse; interocellar furrow shallow and deep, postocellar furrow broad and shallow; postocellar area slightly convex, lower than top of ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[536,619,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="46.[151,249,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,220,1661]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[151,1436,193,1677]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 21. Siobla species, head (dorsal view), postocellar area and mesoscutellum (lateral view). a – c. S. brevipilosa, sp. nov., 3; d – f. S. sinica, sp. nov., Ƥ; g – i. S. sinica, sp. nov., 3; j – l. S. longipennis, sp. nov., Ƥ. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280125/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[590,619,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
b), without middle carina, about 
<number box="[996,1031,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.3">1.3</number>
× as broad as long; lateral furrows deep, slightly curved outwards, divergent posteriorly; head behind eyes equal to half of eyes in length in dorsal view, convex in base and narrowing posteriorly. Occipital groove shallow and weak. Antenna 
<number box="[1215,1250,223,247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.4">1.4</number>
× head and thorax combined in length. Mesoscutellum roundly elevated, not higher than scutum (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1187,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="46.[151,249,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,220,1661]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[151,1436,193,1677]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 21. Siobla species, head (dorsal view), postocellar area and mesoscutellum (lateral view). a – c. S. brevipilosa, sp. nov., 3; d – f. S. sinica, sp. nov., Ƥ; g – i. S. sinica, sp. nov., 3; j – l. S. longipennis, sp. nov., Ƥ. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280125/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[1157,1187,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
c); posttergite without middle carina; metascutellum with a fine middle carina; mesepisternum angularly elevated, without ventral spur. Apex of hind tibia distinctly enlarged; metabasitarsus 
<number box="[764,799,332,356]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.5">4.5</number>
× as long as broad, 
<number box="[1030,1065,332,356]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.8">0.8</number>
× length of remaining 
<number box="[1329,1343,332,356]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
tarsomeres combined; hind inner tibial spur 
<number box="[583,618,367,391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.4">0.4</number>
× length of metabasitarsus. 
<collectingCountry box="[945,1001,367,391]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing with petiole of anal cell shorter than half length of cu-a. Subgenital plate about as broad as long, apical margin round; genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[1279,1363,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="39.[151,249,1611,1634]" captionTargetBox="[213,1392,212,1578]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[193,1393,193,1590]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 14. Siobla species, gonoforcep. a. S. brevipilosa, sp. nov.; b. S. maculipennis, sp. nov.; c. S. metallica; d. S. obtusiscutellata, sp. nov.; e. S. vardalae, sp. nov.; f. S. rugosipropodea, sp. nov.; g. S. shennongjiana, sp. nov.; h. S. sinica, sp. nov.; i. S. reticulatia; j. S. foveata; k. S. leucotarsis, sp. nov.; l. S. caerulea, sp. nov.; m. S. zenaida. Scale bar = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280119/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figs 
<number box="[1334,1363,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
a, 
<number box="[1388,1417,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="15.0">15</number>
a.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,932]" box="[197,417,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,284,440,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Female</emphasis>
