<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,656,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[653,859,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Siobla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiscutellata">
<emphasis box="[653,859,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">S. obtusiscutellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by the following: postocellar area slightly elevated, lower than top of ocelli, interspaces between punctures on the postocellar area shiny; middle fovea broad and deep, not smaller than frontal basin; mesoscutellum almost flat, interspaces of punctures on the mesoscutellum about equal to diameter of the punctures, posttergite without middle carina,; hind tibial spur pale brown. In 
<taxonomicName box="[339,549,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Siobla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiscutellata">
<emphasis box="[339,549,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">S. obtusiscutellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: postocellar area distinctly elevated, higher than top of ocelli, interspaces between punctures on postocellar area of male narrow, microsculptured; middle fovea shallow, obviously smaller than frontal basin; mesoscutellum round, distinctly elevated, interspaces of punctures on mesoscutellum broader than diameter of punctures, posttergite with a middle longitudinal carina; hind tibial spur blackish brown.
</paragraph>
